        "- We maintain a `tail` pointer in the class so that we can begin the backward traversal in O(1) time, without needing to traverse the entire list first.\n",
        "- The bidirectional search visits at most n/2 nodes in the average case, which reduces the number of comparisons compared to a single-direction search.\n",
        "\n",
        "### We do not use a Singly Linked List which is the closest alternative\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
