        "### Algorithm 5: Add Flight to Fleet (Append to Tail)\n",
        "\n",
        "**Goal:** Add a new flight record to the end of the fleet database.  \n",
        "\n",
        "**Steps:**\n",
        "\n",
        "1. We create a new fleet node using the given flight ID, required crew count, and currently assigned crew count.\n",
        "2. We check whether the database is empty. If it is, we set both the head and the tail pointers to the new node, because the new node is simultaneously the first and last entry.\n",
        "3. If the database already has entries, we link the new node backward by setting its prev pointer to the current tail node.\n",
        "4. We then link the current tail node forward by setting its next pointer to the new node.\n",
        "5. Finally, we update the tail pointer to point to the new node, so future appends will always find the end in O(1) time.\n",
        "\n",
        "  \n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "**Pseudocode:**\n",
