        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "<br>\n",
        "\n",
        "### Algorithm 7: Bidirectional Search\n",
        "\n",
        "**Goal:** Search for a flight by placing one pointer at the head and another at the tail, then advancing both toward the center simultaneously.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "**Steps:**\n",
        "\n",
        "1. We check whether the database is empty. If it is, we print a message and return None.\n",
        "2. We place the left pointer at the head node and the right pointer at the tail node.\n",
        "3. We begin a loop that continues as long as both pointers are still pointing to valid nodes.\n",
        "4. At each iteration, we first check whether the node at left matches the target flight ID. If it does, we print a confirmation and return the left node.\n",
        "5. We then check whether the node at right matches the target flight ID. If it does, we print a confirmation and return the right node.\n",
        "6. We then check whether the two pointers have met or become adjacent. If left == right, both pointers are at the same node and we have checked the entire list. If left.next == right, there are no unvisited nodes between them. In either case, we break out of the loop.\n",
        "7. If neither pointer has found the target and the pointers have not crossed, we advance left one step forward using left.next and move right one step backward using right.prev.\n",
        "8. We repeat from step 4.\n",
        "9. If the loop ends without returning a result, we print a not-found message and return None.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Pseudocode:**\n",
        "```\n",
        "FUNCTION bidirectional_search(flight_id):\n",
        "    IF head is None:\n",
        "        PRINT \"Fleet database is empty.\"\n",
        "        RETURN None\n",
        "\n",
        "    left  = head\n",
        "    right = tail\n",
