        "### Algorithms and Pseudocode\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "### Algorithm 9: Check if Queue is Empty\n",
        "\n",
        "The goal is to determine whether the standby queue contains any crewmembers.\n",
        "\n",
        "Steps:\n",
        "* We check if the front pointer of the queue is None.\n",
        "* If it is None, the queue has no nodes and is empty.\n",
        "* Otherwise, at least one node exists in the queue.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Pseudocode\n",
        "```\n",
        "FUNCTION is_empty():\n",
        "    RETURN (front == None)\n",
        "END FUNCTION\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "### Algorithm 10: Enqueue Crewmember (Add to Rear)\n",
        "\n",
        "The goal is to add a new crewmember to the end of the standby queue.\n",
        "\n",
        "Steps:\n",
        "* First we check if the queue is empty.\n",
        "* If it is empty, we assign both front and rear to the new node.\n",
        "* If not, we link the current rear node to the new node using rear.next.\n",
        "* We then update the rear pointer to the new node.\n",
        "\n",
        "###Pseudocode\n",
        "```\n",
        "FUNCTION enqueue(node):\n",
        "    IF front == None:\n",
        "        front = node\n",
        "        rear  = node\n",
        "    ELSE:\n",
        "        rear.next = node\n",
        "        rear      = node\n",
        "END FUNCTION\n",
        "```\n",
        "### Algorithm 11: Dequeue Crewmember (Remove from Front)\n",
        "\n",
        "The goal is to remove and return the crewmember at the front of the queue.\n",
        "\n",
        "Steps:\n",
        "* We first check if the queue is empty. If so, return None.\n",
        "* We store the current front node in a temporary variable (hold).\n",
        "* If the queue has only one node (front.next is None), we also set rear to None.\n",
        "* We move the front pointer to the next node.\n",
        "* We isolate the removed node (hold.next = None).\n",
        "* Finally, we return the removed node.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Pseudocode\n",
        "```\n",
        "FUNCTION dequeue():\n",
        "    IF front == None:\n",
        "        RETURN None\n",
        "\n",
        "    hold = front\n",
        "\n",
        "    IF front.next == None:\n",
        "        rear = None\n",
        "\n",
        "    front = front.next\n",
        "    hold.next = None\n",
        "\n",
        "    RETURN hold\n",
        "END FUNCTION\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "### Algorithm 12: Display Queue\n",
        "\n",
        "This prints all crewmembers in the standby queue in order.\n",
        "\n",
        "Steps:\n",
        "* We check if the queue is empty. If so, print a message.\n",
        "* We set current to the front node.\n",
        "* We traverse the queue node by node.\n",
        "* For each node, we print the member_id and rating.\n",
        "* We continue until current becomes None.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Pseudocode\n",
        "```\n",
        "FUNCTION display():\n",
        "    IF front == None:\n",
        "        PRINT \"No Standby Crewmember\"\n",
        "        RETURN\n",
        "\n",
        "    current = front\n",
        "\n",
        "    WHILE current is not None:\n",
        "        PRINT current.member_id, \"(\", current.rating, \") -> \" (WITHOUT NEW LINE)\n",
        "        current = current.next\n",
        "END FUNCTION\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "### Algorithm 13: Register Standby Crewmember\n",
        "The goal is to insert a new crewmember into the standby queue.\n",
        "\n",
        "Steps:\n",
        "* We create a new CrewNode using member_id and aircraft_rating.\n",
        "* We insert the new node into the queue using the enqueue function.\n",
        "* The queue is updated in-place.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Pseudocode\n",
        "```\n",
        "FUNCTION register_standby_crewmember(member_id, aircraft_rating, standby_queue):\n",
        "    crew_member = CrewNode(member_id, aircraft_rating)\n",
        "    standby_queue.enqueue(crew_member)\n",
        "END FUNCTION\n",
        "```\n",
        "### Algorithm 14: Retrieve Eligible Crew\n",
        "\n",
        "The goal here is finding and removing the first crewmember with a required aircraft rating while preserving the order of remaining crew.\n",
        "\n",
        "Steps:\n",
        "1. We create a new empty queue (new_queue) to temporarily store crewmembers.\n",
        "2. We initialize selected_crew as None.\n",
        "3. We process the entire standby queue, dequeuing one crewmember at a time:\n",
        "4. If the crewmember’s rating matches the required rating and no match has been found yet, we assign this crewmember to selected_crew.\n",
        "5. Otherwise, we enqueue the crewmember into new_queue.\n",
        "6. After processing all nodes, we restore the original queue order by moving all elements from new_queue back into standby_queue.\n",
        "7. We return the selected crewmember.\n",
        "\n",
        "###Pseudocode\n",
        "```\n",
        "FUNCTION retrieve_eligible_crew(standby_queue, required_rating):\n",
        "\n",
        "    new_queue = Queue()\n",
        "    selected_crew = None\n",
        "\n",
        "    WHILE standby_queue is not empty:\n",
        "        crew = standby_queue.dequeue()\n",
        "\n",
        "        IF crew.rating == required_rating AND selected_crew == None:\n",
        "            selected_crew = crew\n",
        "        ELSE:\n",
        "            new_queue.enqueue(crew)\n",
        "\n",
        "    WHILE new_queue is not empty:\n",
        "        standby_queue.enqueue(new_queue.dequeue())\n",
        "\n",
        "    RETURN selected_crew\n",
        "\n",
        "END FUNCTION\n",
        "```\n",
        "### Algorithm 15: Display Standby Pool\n",
        "\n",
        "The goal here is to display all crewmembers in the standby pool by calling the queue’s display function, with appropirate error handling. If an invalid object is passed, an error message is shown.\n",
        "\n",
        "Steps:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. We attempt to call the display() method on the standby_pool.\n",
        "* If the standby_pool is a valid Queue object, its crewmembers are printed.\n",
        "* If an error occurs (like if it was invalid input), we catch the exception and print an error message.\n",
        "### Pseudocode\n",
        "```\n",
        "FUNCTION display_standby_pool(standby_pool):\n",
        "\n",
        "    TRY:\n",
        "        CALL standby_pool.display()\n",
        "    CATCH error:\n",
        "        PRINT \"Please pass in the standby_pool Queue\"\n",
        "\n",
        "END FUNCTION\n",
        "```"
